[CHALLENGE] Find Fibonacci Projects · L1 · sql

Fix the query to return all rows from Projects where the name contains 'Fibonacci', ordered by project_id ascending.

[CHALLENGE] Recent Paid Invoices for Fibonacci Projects per Customer · L3 · sql

SQLite tables: Customers(id, name), Projects(id, customer_id, name), Invoices(id, project_id, amount, invoice_date, status).
Task: Using CTEs, return one row per customer who has at least one project whose name contains 'Fibo' (case-insensitive), with:
- customer_name
- project_count (distinct matching projects)
- total_invoiced_amount (sum of PAID invoices in the last 365 days for those projects; 0 if none)
- last_invoice_date (max recent PAID invoice date; NULL if none)
Order by total_invoiced_amount DESC, then customer_name ASC.

code:
WITH recent AS (
  SELECT *
  FROM Invoice
  WHERE status = 'PAID'
    AND invoice_date >= date('now','-365 days')
),
fibo_projects AS (
  SELECT *
  FROM Projects
  WHERE name LIKE '%Fibo%'
)
SELECT
  c.name AS customer_name,
  COUNT(p.id) AS project_count,
  SUM(r.amount) AS total_invoiced_amount,
  MAX(r.invoice_date) AS last_invoice_date
FROM Customers c
JOIN fibo_projects p ON p.id = c.id
JOIN recent r ON r.id = p.id
GROUP BY customer_name
ORDER BY total_invoiced_amount DESC, customer_name;

code:
WITH recent_invoices AS (
  SELECT i.*
  FROM Invoices i
  WHERE i.status = 'PAID'
    AND i.invoice_date >= date('now','-365 days')
),
fibo_projects AS (
  SELECT p.*
  FROM Projects p
  WHERE lower(p.name) LIKE '%fibo%'
)
SELECT
  c.name AS customer_name,
  COUNT(DISTINCT p.id) AS project_count,
  COALESCE(SUM(ri.amount), 0) AS total_invoiced_amount,
  MAX(ri.invoice_date) AS last_invoice_date
FROM Customers c
JOIN fibo_projects p ON p.customer_id = c.id
LEFT JOIN recent_invoices ri ON ri.project_id = p.id
GROUP BY c.id, c.name
ORDER BY total_invoiced_amount DESC, customer_name ASC;
